title: President Obama Announces Presidential Delegation to Uruguay to Attend the Inauguration of His Excellency Jose Mujica | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
February 25, 2010

 



President Obama Announces Presidential Delegation to Uruguay to Attend the Inauguration of His Excellency Jose Mujica




WASHINGTON--President Barack Obama today announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to Montevideo, Uruguay, to attend the Inauguration of His Excellency Jose Mujica, President-elect of the Oriental Republic of Uruguay on March 1, 2010.
The Honorable Hillary Rodham Clinton, Secretary of State, will lead the delegation.
MEMBERS OF THE PRESIDENTIAL DELEGATION:
The Honorable David D. Nelson, U.S. Ambassador to the Oriental Republic of Uruguay
	The Honorable Carmen Lomellin, U.S. Permanent Representative to the Organization of American States
